What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Micro-Invasive Glaucoma Implants Market?

Micro-Invasive Glaucoma Implants Market Analysis

The micro-invasive glaucoma implants market is experiencing substantial growth due to the rising prevalence of glaucoma and the increasing demand for minimally invasive surgical options. Micro-invasive glaucoma implants offer effective treatment solutions by providing controlled intraocular pressure reduction with minimal tissue disruption. Recent developments in this market include innovations such as the Hydrus Micro-Stent, which received FDA approval for its ability to improve outflow in the eye's drainage system, and advancements by companies such as Glaukos Corporation, which is pioneering new technologies in minimally invasive glaucoma surgery (MIGS). The market's expansion is further supported by increasing healthcare investments and a shift toward outpatient procedures. As more patients seek less invasive alternatives to traditional glaucoma surgeries, the adoption of micro-invasive implants is expected to rise, driven by their advantages in safety, efficacy, and reduced recovery times. These trends underscore the market’s dynamic growth and the ongoing innovation in glaucoma management technologies.

Micro-Invasive Glaucoma Implants Market Size

The global micro-invasive glaucoma implants market size was valued at USD 318.19 million in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 2611.66 million by 2031, with a CAGR of 30.10% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework.

